Description: Sherd of rim of East Greek pottery krater; maeander pattern on top, dots on outside; roughly glazed on underside; graffito on top of rim.
Curator's comments: Marked in pencil '6', with some lines before it. Probably from same krater as 1888,0601.708a-c.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.999)
